{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place gelatine leaves into a ceramic or glass bowl and cover with cold water. Leave to soak until gelatine leaves have softened and swelled.","Place hazelnuts into mixing bowl and chop <b>8 sec\/speed 7<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Without rinsing mixing bowl, <strong>insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place cream into mixing bowl and whip <b>until cream has thickened\/speed 3<b>, watching cream carefully through hole in mixing bowl lid to avoid overwhipping (approx. 2-3 minutes). <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Transfer into a separate bowl, cover with plastic wrap and place into refrigerator.","Without rinsing mixing bowl, <strong>re-insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place egg yolks, caster sugar and vanilla bean paste and cook <b>9 min\/70°C\/speed 3<b>.","Squeeze the gelatine leaves to remove excess water. Add squeezed gelatine leaves and ¾ of the reserved hazelnuts and mix <b>30 sec\/speed 3<b>. Transfer mixture into a large bowl. Set remaining ¼ of the hazelnuts aside for garnishing.","Fold in the reserved whipped cream to hazelnut mixture. Lightly brush water or rum into 8 individual ramekins (6-8 cm), then transfer Bavarian mixture into them. Cover ramekins with plastic wrap and place into refrigerator for a minimum 6 hours.","Once set, remove from refrigerator and garnish with remaining hazelnuts before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["4 titanium strength gelatine leaves","100 g hazelnuts, toasted","500 g pouring (whipping) cream, chilled","6 egg yolks","120 g caster sugar","1 tsp vanilla bean paste","1 tbsp water"]}],"id":"r98825","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-QRyxLQeSoMc\/XZaocOguU5I\/AAAAAAAAhKM\/xMTD4oYVCPki3sMuG4nSDG6EA7jzusGcQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_oNfbEE7lUjLWaeGM.png","title":"Hazelnut Bavarian","publishedAt":"2015-08-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6.5 g","fat":"33.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"17.3 g","calories":"1629 kJ \/ 388 kcal"},"usefulItems":"ceramic or glass bowl, plastic wrap, large bowl, 8 ramekins, pastry brush, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["<strong>Chocolate Bavarian:<\/strong> substitute the hazelnuts with 100 g chocolate, broken into pieces. Grate chocolate <strong>8 sec\/speed 7<\/strong> in step 1, then proceed as per recipe.","<strong>Vanilla Bavarian:<\/strong> omit the hazelnuts in step 2. Substitute the vanilla paste with 1 whole vanilla bean pod, seeds scraped and proceed as per recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","6h 25m","8 portion"]}